Text.Value: *The ache builds as you squeeze your hands together. Were your fingers always so thick, your skin always so sticky?*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CINE_Ground_Idle pose player shakily rubs their hands. ~CDavis

Text.Value: Take it. One motion. Across the neck.
Wipe the sweat from your brow.
Don't you see how far gone you are? Give me that blade - I'll make it quick.
I will wait. But know this: I am watching. If the sickness does not pass come dawn...
Vlaakith gha'g shkath zai!

EditorData.AnimationTags: Player throws Lae'Zel off and enters a combat stance. ~CDavis
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The player throws Laezel off and takes a combative stance
EditorData.NodeContext: VLAH-kith gawg shkaath ZAI! For the honour of Vlaakith!

Text.Value: Be strong. You will survive this. You will please your queen!
*A shadow swims across your vision, and a familiar voice tells you to be calm. You are loved.*
*Your finger traces the arc of your lips. Wetness: sweat, blood, and saliva mixed into one viscous liquid.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CINE_Ground_Idle pose player shakily rubs their lips. ~CDavis

Text.Value: Chk - a splendid ruse. My anger is surpassed only by my respect.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~Player stows blade and rises with Lazael
EditorData.NodeContext: You deceived her. Lae'zel is both angry and impressed.

Text.Value: *Your minds intertwine. You sense a touch of uncertainty, a touch of disgust.*
*The world swims as you close, then reopen your eyes. How long have you been waiting here? A moment? A night? A tenday?*

EditorData.AnimationTags: CINE_Ground_Idle pose player shakes their head trying to find their bearings. ~CDavis
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The player shakes their head trying to find their bearings

Text.Value: I will not let the ghaik take me. I will earn Vlaakith's honour.
*A shiver runs across your mind... You feel sated.*
I will not be ghaik. Vlaakith gha'g shkath zai!

EditorData.AnimationTags: The player slits Lae'Zel's throat. Does out of duty, not murderous intent. ~CDavis
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~Player executes Lae'zel with one slice of the blade.
EditorData.NodeContext: VLAH-kith gawg shkaath ZAI! For the honour of Vlaakith!

Text.Value: *The air is heavy. Moisture drips down your forehead; pain shoots through your fingers.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: Player Stumbles through forest, slumps down onto their butt against a tree. End in CINE_Ground_Idle pose. ~CDavis
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: ~The player stumbles through the forest, proping themselves against a tree

Text.Value: *The great warrior Lae'zel, a failure to her kind. She will wield no silver sword, ride no red dragon, forever unknown to the great lich queen Vlaakith.*
Blink away the discomfort.
Can you feel it crawling through you? Tendrils squirming in your chest, gripping your heart, piercing your belly? Your bones popping, your flesh swelling?

EditorData.stateContext: LZ has handed the player her knife,

Text.Value: *Your mind lurches, reeling suddenly as if... bitten.*
This is not exhaustion. This is ceremorphosis.
Close your eyes. Submit.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Lae'Zel and the player rise up from the ground, Lae'Zel hands the player her knife. ~CDavis

Text.Value: Ch'k'l ghaik Vlaakith m' zath'ak!

Text.Value: No one is dying tonight. We still have time.
Rub your aching hands.
Explore Lae'zel's mind.
Surrender to Lae'zel. You will not become an abomination.
*Something stirs deep within you, hungry and alert... it's taking something you'll never get back.*
This is no simple fever. This is ceremorphosis.
It's just a fever. Rest will break it.
Bah - I cannot trust my own mind. So it seems I must trust yours.
The monster in you craves birth. I trust no one but me to deny it.
...I will end us all.
I will be quick with my blade. First you. Then the others. Then myself.
Press your fingers to your mouth.
First you. Then myself.
*The presence deep in your mind is awake, unblinking. This is it. A single word pervades your consciousness: 'Soon'.*
*Your blood runs quicker, feeding the gnawing absence at the centre of your mind.*
*Lae'zel's fear grips you. Not fear of death, but fear of insignificance.*
It feels as if a snake is slithering through every limb. My throat burns like flames erupted within.
Attack Lae'zel.

EditorData.stateContext: The player sits by themselves trying to identify the source of their illness

Text.Value: *Your hands shake as they reach upward. Your forehead remains drenched, no matter how much you wipe.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: In CINE_Ground_Idle pose player shakily wipes forehead. ~CDavis

Text.Value: I can. I see it in you. I feel it in me. We are lost.
Slit her throat.
Explore Lae'zel's mind.
We're just exhausted. Lower the blade before you do something foolish.
*Lae'zel's mind holds you at length. Her thoughts remain unknown.*
*Your mind is full, bursting with ecstasy and terror. Finally, it is coming. You are becoming.*

Synopsis: Lae'zel approaches you in camp. You are showing symptoms of ceremorphosis. So is everyone else. She threatens to kill everyone unless you convince her to stand down. She is afraid, though does not wish you to know it.
